    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 2a, 3: immunogold EM showed SAD-B (BRSK1) particles at synaptic vesicles, authors remark partial enrichment at the active zone (but only few EM images are shown and no quantification of puncta). \"Note that several signals of SAD-B were also detected in the dendrites (Figure 2A) and cell bodies (data not shown)\"\n\nFigure 2b,c: SAD-B (BRSK1) was enriched in both the synaptic vesicle fraction and PSD fractions of rat brain homogenate.. Experimental description: Results, Figure 2 legend: \"The homogenate of rat brain was subjected to subcellular fractionation. \"\n\nantibody:\n\"Rabbit antisera against SAD-B were raised against GST-SAD-B (aa 450-521; the anti-SAD-B Ab and aa 548-720; the anti-SCR2 Ab) and affinity purified as previously described (Deguchi-Tawarada et al., 2004).\"",
